    <section style="padding-top:0px;"> 
     <div class="page-header" id="about" style="margin-top:5px"> 
      <h1>What's College For?</h1> 
     </div> 
     <div class="row"> 
      <div class="span12"> 
       <img src="../../img/OR11_0298_700.jpg" alt="OR11_0298_700" width="700" height="325"> 
       <h3>What’s the first question people ask </h3> 
       <blockquote>
        <p id="footnote1-ref">“The qualities that employers seek are the concern and result not so much of specialized education as of liberal education.” <small><a href="#footnote1">[1] Henry Ford</a></small></p>
       </blockquote> 
       <p>when you start talking about college? <em>Where are you going?</em></p> 
       <p>But before you think about where you’re going to college, <strong>you should think about why</strong> you’re going to college.</p> 
       <p>If you ask yourself <strong>“What’s college for?”</strong> that will help you decide where to go.</p> 
       <p>One obvious answer to “What’s college for?” is: a job. Let’s start there.</p> 
      </div> 
     </div>
     <!-- /row --> 
     <!--
